  "text": "Increasing the dose of second-generation H1 antihistamines up to fourfold is a relatively new recommendation. Nevertheless, physicians are not sufficiently confident to use this approach, in part because increasing the dose of antihistamines improves the control of pruritus significantly but does not reduce the number of wheals [CITATION_1] . Moreover, the weaknesses of clinical studies and their significant heterogeneity limits the consistency of findings to support this approach [CITATION_2] . The fear of possible side effects using higher doses of secondgeneration H1 antihistamines is another important factor among physicians [CITATION_3] .",
